Great question, Jeff. In the Tempest API, the obs section returns an array of weather observation values in a specific order—each index corresponds to a different parameter. For a Tempest device (obs_st), here’s what each index represents:
0- Timestamp (Epoch, UTC)
1- Wind lull (m/s)
2- Wind average (m/s)
3- Wind gust (m/s)
4- Wind direction (degrees)
5- Wind sample interval (seconds)
6- Pressure (mb)
7- Air temperature (°C)
8- Relative humidity (%)
9- Illuminance (lux)
10- UV index
11- Solar radiation (W/m²)
12- Rain accumulation during interval (mm)
13- Precipitation type (0 = none, 1 = rain, 2 = hail, 3 = rain + hail)
14- Lightning average distance (km)
15- Lightning strike count
16- Battery voltage (V)
17- Reporting interval (minutes)
18- Local day rain accumulation (mm)
19- Nearcast rain accumulation (mm)
20- Local day Nearcast rain accumulation (mm)
21- Precipitation analysis type (0 = none, 1 = Nearcast w/ display on, 2 = Nearcast w/ display off
